<subSubSection id="49C942EEFFB7396FEBD2C61DFA6759D5" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" type="description">
<paragraph id="016C1165FFB7396FEBD2C61DFDCA5A7E" blockId="25.[227,565,302,328]" box="[227,565,302,328]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<heading id="5A24A609FFB7396FEBD2C61DFDCA5A7E" bold="true" box="[227,565,302,328]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" reason="3">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFB7396FEBD2C61DFDCA5A7E" bold="true" box="[227,565,302,328]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
Dimensions of the 
<typeStatus id="DE68AFC7FFB7396FEAF8C61DFDCA5A7E" box="[457,565,302,328]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">holotype</typeStatus>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="016C1165FFB7396FEBD2C66EFC555A4E" blockId="25.[227,938,349,376]" box="[227,938,349,376]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
Length = 
<quantity id="C62BBC80FFB7396FEA64C66EFE3E5A4E" box="[341,449,349,376]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.2" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" unit="mm" value="8.2">8.20 mm</quantity>
; height = 
<quantity id="C62BBC80FFB7396FE904C66EFD5E5A4E" box="[565,673,349,376]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.68" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" unit="mm" value="3.68">3.68 mm</quantity>
; thickness = 
<quantity id="C62BBC80FFB7396FE80BC66EFC5A5A4E" box="[826,933,349,376]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.27" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" unit="mm" value="1.27">1.27 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="016C1165FFB7396FEBD2C6ACFE8B5A8F" blockId="25.[227,372,415,441]" box="[227,372,415,441]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<heading id="5A24A609FFB7396FEBD2C6ACFE8B5A8F" bold="true" box="[227,372,415,441]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" reason="3">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFB7396FEBD2C6ACFE8B5A8F" bold="true" box="[227,372,415,441]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="016C1165FFB7396FEBD2C6FDFA6759D5" blockId="25.[226,1437,462,739]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
This species is characterized by thin, very elongate otoliths which are obtuse at both ends, but the anterior one is more pointed. The deepest part of the otoliths is in their central part, which feature is most evident in the 
<typeStatus id="DE68AFC7FFB7396FEAB6C525FE0D5906" box="[391,498,534,560]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">holotype</typeStatus>
. All the margins are smooth. The inner face is very slightly convex and the outer face is nearly flat. The sulcus is well-divided into ostium and cauda and opens widely antero-dorsally on the anterior rim. A large and oval ostial colliculum fills the ostium. The ostial crista superior curves markedly upwards. The cauda is long and straight, without colliculum. The caudal crista superior is more developed than the crista inferior and markedly constricted and ventrally bent in the posterior part. The crista inferior is almost straight without constriction. The ventral area is larger than the dorsal one.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="49C942EEFFB7396FEBD2C438FADF58D5" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="016C1165FFB7396FEBD2C438FEAA5813" blockId="25.[227,341,779,805]" box="[227,341,779,805]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<heading id="5A24A609FFB7396FEBD2C438FEAA5813" bold="true" box="[227,341,779,805]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" reason="3">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFB7396FEBD2C438FEAA5813" bold="true" box="[227,341,779,805]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="016C1165FFB7396FEBD2C40AFADF58D5" blockId="25.[226,1437,825,995]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
The otoliths of this new species are clearly different from those of the more commonly co-occurring 
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FFB7396FEBD4C46EFD475841" authority="(Koken, 1884)" baseAuthorityName="Koken" baseAuthorityYear="1884" box="[229,696,861,887]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Albulidae" genus="Pterothrissus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Albuliformes" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="umbonatus">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFB7396FEBD4C46EFDF65841" box="[229,521,861,887]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Pterothrissus umbonatus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="65426C94FFB7396FE927C46EFD4F5841" author="Koken" box="[534,688,861,887]" firstAuthor="Koken" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="500 - 565" refId="ref54572" refString="Koken E. 1884. Ueber Fisch-Otolithen, insbesondere uber diejenige der norddeutschen Oligocan- Ablagerungen. Zeitschrift der deutschen geologischen Gesellschaft 36: 500 - 565." type="journal article" year="1884">Koken, 1884</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
(see below) by their slender appearance. 
<bibRefCitation id="65426C94FFB7396FEFAEC46EFA625841" author="Schwarzhans" box="[1183,1437,861,887]" firstAuthor="Schwarzhans" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="77 - 91" refId="ref56652" refString="Schwarzhans W. 1981 a. Die Entwicklung der Familie Pterothrissidae (Elopomorpha; Pisces), rekonstruiert nach Otolithen. Senckenbergiana lethaea 62 (2 - 6): 77 - 91." type="journal article" year="1981" yearSuffix="a">Schwarzhans (1981a)</bibRefCitation>
indicated 
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FFB7396FEA64C4B2FCF258AA" authority="Stinton, 1975" authorityName="Stinton" authorityYear="1975" box="[341,781,897,924]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Albulidae" genus="Pterothrissus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Albuliformes" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="protensus">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFB7396FEA64C4B2FD9858AD" box="[341,615,897,923]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Pterothrissus protensus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="65426C94FFB7396FE95CC4B2FCF258AA" author="Stinton" box="[621,781,897,924]" firstAuthor="Stinton" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="1 - 56" refId="ref57487" refString="Stinton F. C. 1975. Fish otoliths from the English Eocene (part 1). Palaeontographical Society Monographs 544: 1 - 56." type="journal article" year="1975">Stinton, 1975</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FFB7396FEF36C4B2FED95889" authority="(Leriche, 1908)" baseAuthorityName="Leriche" baseAuthorityYear="1908" class="Actinopterygii" family="Albulidae" genus="Pterothrissus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Albuliformes" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tardinensis">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFB7396FEF36C4B2FAD558AD" box="[1031,1322,897,923]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Pterothrissus tardinensis</emphasis>
(Leriche, 1908)
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation id="65426C94FFB7396FEA52C496FD7C5889" author="Nolf &amp; Rundle" box="[355,643,933,959]" firstAuthor="Nolf" page="19" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="12 - 46" refId="ref56150" refString="Nolf D. &amp; Rundle A. 2018. Fish otoliths from the Paleocene and basal Ypresian of the North Sea Basin and dependencies (London Basin, Belgium, Paris Basin). Bulletin d'Information des Geologues du Bassin de Paris 55: 12 - 46." type="journal article" year="2018">Nolf &amp; Rundle 2018: 19</bibRefCitation>
), as the 
<typeStatus id="DE68AFC7FFB7396FE9D2C496FCE95889" box="[739,790,933,959]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">type</typeStatus>
species of 
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FFB7396FE8A9C496FBC65889" authorityName="Schwarzhans" authorityYear="1981" box="[920,1081,933,959]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Albulidae" genus="Elopothrissus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Albuliformes" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFB7396FE8A9C496FBC65889" box="[920,1081,933,959]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Elopothrissus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The otoliths of 
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FFB7396FEFCBC495FA635889" baseAuthorityName="Leriche" baseAuthorityYear="1908" box="[1274,1436,933,959]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Albulidae" genus="Pterothrissus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Albuliformes" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tardinensis">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFB7396FEFCBC495FA635889" box="[1274,1436,933,959]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">E. tardinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are thicker and much more convex on the outer face than those of 
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FFB7396FE8DAC4FAFB4158D4" authority="Lin &amp; Nolf &amp; Steurbaut, 2022" authorityName="Lin &amp; Nolf &amp; Steurbaut" authorityYear="2022" box="[1003,1214,968,994]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Albulidae" genus="Elopothrissus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Albuliformes" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bernardlemorti" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFB7396FE8DAC4FAFB4158D4" box="[1003,1214,968,994]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">E. bernardlemorti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="2894700CFFB7396FEFF4C4FAFADF58D5" box="[1221,1312,969,995]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
